article.headline: Radford 78, VA Intermont 66
article.story:
RADFORD, Va. (AP) -- Chris Oliver and Whit Holcomb-Faye each had
26 points to lead Radford to a 78-66 win over Virginia Intermont on
Thursday night.

With 14 assists, Oliver recorded his fifth double-double in the
last six games for the Highlanders (6-3).

Juan Ornelas led the Cobras (3-8) with 29 points, and Chris
Babbit added 16.

Radford led the entire game, 31-22 going into halftime. The
Highlanders had its largest lead of 16 with 7:41 remaining in the
game.

The Cobras were 44.6 percent from the field, and Radford was
43.9 percent shooting. The Highlander scored 17 points off of
Virginia Intermont's 17 turnovers.

Oliver made the last field goal for Radford, putting the team up
76-61 with 1:26 remaining. The Cobras scored last with a 3-pointer
from Ornelas with 33 seconds remaining.
